{
  "slug": "structured-output-is-a-contract",
  "title": "Structured output is a contract",
  "category": "ai",
  "kicker": "AI interfaces",
  "hook": "A model that returns almost-JSON is not integrated. It is freelancing inside your parser.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-21",
  "tags": [
    "structured-output",
    "schemas"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Text is a terrible API boundary",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Free-form text is great for humans and slippery for code. The moment another service depends on the shape, the answer needs a schema, validation, retries, and a failure path.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "parser · almost works",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "$ node parse-answer.mjs",
              "c": "pr"
            },
            {
              "t": "expected: {\"priority\":\"high\",\"owner\":\"billing\"}",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "got: \"Sure, priority is probably high.\"",
              "c": "err"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "graph",
          "center": "model loop",
          "nodes": [
            "prompt",
            "retrieval",
            "tools",
            "memory",
            "policy",
            "evals"
          ],
          "caption": "Hit the button and watch the hidden AI surface area light up.",
          "action": "stress the agent",
          "idle": "guardrails armed",
          "running": "probing weak edges...",
          "done": "6 AI failure paths exposed"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Make the shape explicit",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Define the fields, allowed values, and nullable cases before calling the model. Then validate the response like any other external dependency.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "schemas/triage.json",
          "code": "{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\"priority\", \"owner\", \"reason\"],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"priority\": { \"enum\": [\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\"] }\n  }\n}",
          "caption": "A schema turns vibes into a contract your app can reject."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Reject invalid answers loudly",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">If the model misses the schema, do not patch around it downstream. Retry with the validation error, fall back to a human path, or fail the job with a useful log.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "lab",
          "title": "AI launch switchboard",
          "caption": "Flip the switches and watch the story turn into a tiny operating model.",
          "toggles": [
            {
              "label": "source checks",
              "off": "answers from vibe",
              "on": "evidence gate on",
              "weight": 26
            },
            {
              "label": "tool policy",
              "off": "model can ask for anything",
              "on": "permissions checked outside model",
              "weight": 28
            },
            {
              "label": "eval replay",
              "off": "demo path only",
              "on": "failure cases replayed",
              "weight": 24
            },
            {
              "label": "human handoff",
              "off": "bot traps edge cases",
              "on": "risky cases route out",
              "weight": 22
            }
          ],
          "minLabel": "sloppy",
          "maxLabel": "shippable",
          "low": "fragile: the model is still freelancing without enough checks",
          "mid": "better: useful guardrails are catching the obvious mistakes",
          "high": "ready-ish: evidence, policy, and evals are all in the loop"
        },
        {
          "type": "stats",
